{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771254372,"nonce":"hrYR8OfjEI/rgh1YOFdXT65cQGg=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87rVQRr","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/212","origin":"github"},"title":"CLAUDE.md tells agents to use `pre-commit run` but pre-commit is not on PATH","message":"## Problem\n\nCLAUDE.md's \"Build \u0026 Test\" section tells agents to run:\n\n```bash\npre-commit run --all-files\n```\n\nBut `pre-commit` is installed in `.venv/bin/pre-commit`, not on the system PATH. The `env.sh` script creates a shell function wrapper to expose it, but Claude Code's Bash tool (and other agent frameworks) don't preserve shell state between calls — each invocation is a fresh shell. So the function is lost immediately after the `source env.sh` call.\n\nThis causes agents to repeatedly get `command not found` errors and attempt to install pre-commit globally.\n\n## Solution\n\nReplace `pre-commit run --all-files` with `make lint` in CLAUDE.md. The Makefile already hardcodes the `.venv/bin/pre-commit` path and auto-bootstraps the venv if missing, so it works reliably from any fresh shell.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}